---


Author Name: **Pinhas Krengel**
Original Redmine Message: 1072 from https://www.veripool.org



---

I have downloaded and installed on my debian machine verilator (using apt-get install).
It works fine with simple examples, but fails when I use DPI System Task/Functions.
It compiles okay but fails in run time, because an export task function is not found:
"Testbench C called t_gen_stim but no such DPI export function name exists in ANY model."

I have a SV bench, which calls a verilog DUT. The bench includes a task:

```
  export "DPI-C" task t_gen_stim;
  task t_gen_stim;
    input bit trd;
    input bit twr;
    $display("task drive %d %d at %d", trd, twr, $time);
    Trd=trd;
    Twr=twr;
  endtask

```

I have included the headers in my cpp bench as described in man pages:

```
#include "Vpipe_fifo_tool.h"
#include "Vpipe_fifo_tool__Dpi.h"
#include "svdpi.h"
#include "verilated.h"
...
  svSetScope (svGetScopeFromName ("u_dut"));

  while (!Verilated::gotFinish()) {
...
     t_gen_stim(entry.rd, entry.wr);

```

This is my compile and run script:
```
clear;/usr/bin/verilator --trace --trace-depth 1 -sv -I./ --cc pipe_fifo_tool.sv --exe sim_main.cpp
cd obj_dir
make -f Vpipe_fifo_tool.mk Vpipe_fifo_tool && echo "make ended ok"

```

Can you please help me to figure out what I do wrong.

